Rating: 0
Ok, I used this as a base and created my own variation. Everything is the same but these three things: I used 1/2 cup splenda and 1/2 cup sugar, and I added 1/3 cup peanut butter to the butter mixture, and I added about 1/4 cup more flour, and I just used chocolate chunks and no peanut chips. I loved them! I wanted to have a little peanut butter flavor in them but I don't like peanut butter chips because of how unnatural they taste. They came out pretty cakey, which was fantastic! I know there are a lot of deviations- wanted to give it a review anyway!

