Rating: 4
I have made these cookies many many times over the past 10 years and they always turn out fabulous and do not last long in my house. Whether you take them out at 10 minutes or bake them til 12, they are always great. I also love to just use chocolate chips and add dried cherries - YUM! They're my "go-to" cookie.

Rating: 3
Made these with Hershey's Special Dark cocoa powder, which made them especially dark and chocolaty. Added some extra flour, per the other reviewers' suggestions, as well as some extra cocoa (no more than 1/4 extra, flour & cocoa combined); baked for only 10 minutes. So far, 15 minutes out of the oven, they're great (for a simple, everyday cookie). I'm taking them to a party tonight... On a side note, I sure wish someone besides Reese's would make peanut-butter chips. Theirs just are not peanut-buttery enough, in my opinion. But that's nothing to do with this recipe--these are very good cookies. If you don't like peanut butter, or you're making them for someone with allergies, you could always substitute white chocolate chips.

Rating: 4
Decadent..sweet...sweet...grab a glass of milk. Be prepared the cookie dough is very dry and it was difficult to mix all the chips into the dough. I left out maybe 1/4 cup of the chips and they were not missed. I cooked my cookies for 14min versus the 12min and they looked pretty uncooked, but that is only because they are a chewy cookie so I do not recommend cooking them anything past the 14mins. Let them cool and they are quite soft and chewy. Everyone raved over them...will definitely make again.

