I added a 1/4 cup extra flour, used salted butter and ditched the extra salt, used 11 oz. of chocolate chips only (I didn't have PB chips on hand), formed the cookies with the large side of my melon baller, and cooked for exactly 10 minutes...and...WOW! SO yummy! Very sweet, so the smaller size is just perfect. Very easy recipe with delicious and sweet results!

